<title>PORTUGAL: Portugal's CMVM suspends trade in CPP.</title>
<headline>Portugal's CMVM suspends trade in CPP.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-07-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Portugal's Financial Markets Committee (CMVM) said it suspended trade in Credito Predial Portugues (CPP) as of 1745 GMT today due to a bid, a CMVM official told Reuters.</p>
<p>Portuguese banks Banco Totta e Acores and Banco Pinto &amp; Sotto Mayor, jointly with Mundial Confianca, which belong to businessman Antonio Champalimaud, will launch a public offer to buy (OPA) for Totta's subsidiary CPP, the Champalimaud group said earlier.</p>
<p>The price of the OPA was 1,800 escudos per share, a statement said.</p>
<p>-- Lisbon newsroom +(351-1) 3538254</p>
